I"0<h1 id="technical-writers">Technical Writers</h1>

<h2 id="quick-tips">Quick tips</h2>

<h3 id="company-terminology"><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/company-terminology/">Company terminology</a></h3>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/company-terminology/#capitalize-human">Make sure to properly capitalize HUMAN and HUMAN’s product names.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/company-terminology/#product-names">Don’t abbreviate HUMAN’s product names.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/company-terminology/#internal-vs-external-names">Don’t use internal product codenames in public-facing documentation.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/company-terminology/#HUMAN-doesnt-block">HUMAN’s products don’t “block” traffic.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/company-terminology/#bots-arent-always-bad">Not all bots are bad.</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="grammar"><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/grammar/">Grammar</a></h3>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/grammar/#active-and-passive-voice">Use the active voice whenever possible.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/grammar/#second-person-pronouns">Use second-person pronouns like <em>you</em> and <em>your</em> to address the reader.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/grammar/#singular-they">Use the singular <em>they</em> as a gender-neutral pronoun.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/grammar/#american-english">Use standard American English spelling conventions.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/grammar/#present-tense">Use the present tense whenever possible.</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="punctuation"><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/punctuation/">Punctuation</a></h3>

<ul>
  <li><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/punctuation/#serial-commas">Use serial commas.</a></li>
</ul>

<h3 id="tone-and-content"><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/tone-and-content/">Tone and content</a></h3>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/tone-and-content/#be-friendly">Strive for an approachable, friendly tone.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/tone-and-content/#write-for-non-experts">Write for a broad audience, not just for experts.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/tone-and-content/#filler-words">Avoid filler words.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/tone-and-content/#simple-vs.-complex">Try to use short, simple words instead of complex, abstract words.</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="formatting-and-organization"><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/">Formatting and organization</a></h3>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/#introduce-code-samples">Introduce code samples with a summary or description of what the code does.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/#captions">Put captions after their associated image.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/#when-to-use-screenshots">Use screenshots sparingly.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/#descriptive-link-text">Use descriptive link text.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/#introduce-procedures">Introduce procedural instructions with a summary or description of what the procedure is for.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/#title-capitalization">Use title case for titles.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/#heading-capitalization">Use sentence case for headings.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/formatting-and-organization/#include-descriptions-after-every-heading">After each heading, include a summary or description of the following section.</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="user-interfaces"><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/user-interfaces/">User interfaces</a></h3>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/user-interfaces/#bold-ui-elements">If the reader must interact with a specific UI element, put the name of that UI element in bold.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/user-interfaces/#task-oriented-instructions">Try to write task-oriented instructions.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/user-interfaces/#angle-brackets">Use angle brackets to describe the process of navigating multiple menu items in a row.</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/user-interfaces/#select-vs-click">Use <em>select</em> instead of <em>click</em>.</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="apis-and-sdks"><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/apis-and-sdks/">APIs and SDKs</a></h3>

<ul>
  <li><a href="/styleguidetemplate/tw/api-reference/#describe-almost-everything">Describe (almost) everything.</a></li>
</ul>

